treet\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"Summarised account: victim in a local coffee shop when an older man starts to interrogate her about where she is from and rants about the problems immigrants are causing in British society. The man grabbed her arm and told her to 'Leave'.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-01T19:35:36.918Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-08-02T05:48:02.004Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":530,\"lat\":\"51.576451\",\"lng\":\"0.021154\",\"date\":\"2016-07-23T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London Borough of Redbridge\",\"description\":\"Racial abuse witnessed in a doctors surgery waiting room. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-01T19:37:15.055Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-08-02T05:48:13.480Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":531,\"lat\":\"51.3492\",\"lng\":\"-1.99271\",\"date\":\"2016-07-24T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Wiltshire\",\"description\":\"Hello, from the middle of nowhere in Wiltshire where I just found a guy at the convenience store in tears because of the racist shite he'd just encountered. He said she'd (previous customer) handed the receipt as if he was contaminated. He said he'd be out of here soon due to the referendum #ashamedtobebritish\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Wiltshire\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-01T19:40:33.210Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-08-02T05:48:44.880Z\",\"support\":\"I gave him a hug, as ever over egging the pudding.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":568,\"lat\":\"55.953252\",\"lng\":\"-3.188267\",\"date\":\"2016-06-24T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Edinburgh\",\"description\":\"Summary FB user (2/3) set up a poll amongst friends and got reports of people being verbally abused in Edinburgh, spat at, and also reports of racist abuse in London (number and nature unspecified)\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Edinburgh\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Source: Worrying Signs\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-03T13:59:14.165Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-08-03T13:59:14.165Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":570,\"lat\":\"51.335545\",\"lng\":\"1.419895\",\"date\":\"2016-08-03T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Thanet District\",\"description\":\"Lady hassled quite aggressively about her background by a UKIP member on a train Ramsgate – Canterbury. The man got off at Canterbury. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Kent\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-03T15:29:22.501Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-08-07T03:03:43.964Z\",\"support\":\"Afterwards, several passengers offered support and contact details as witnesses.\\r\\n\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":571,\"lat\":\"53.527039\",\"lng\":\"-2.28064\",\"date\":\"2016-07-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Bury District\",\"description\":\"Mum and son racially abused in the street by man who told them to 'go home' because he had voted to leave the EU. A mum was subjected to a vile racist rant in the street before the yob told her ‘to go home’ because he had voted for leave in the EU referendum.\\r\\n\\r\\nBritish-born Bangladeshi woman Arry Nessa, 35, and nine-year-old Kalib were walking their usual route to school along Bury New Road in Prestwich when they were confronted by the man who unleashed a sickening verbal attack on the pair, calling Arry a ‘n*****’, ‘immigrant’ and ‘c***’. He then said: “I voted for you to leave so what are you doing here?”\\r\\n\\r\\nArry, a project manager for an art project that works with south Asian families in Rossendale, says she stood up for herself, telling him she was none of those and that she was not afraid of him. She said he then went on to push and shove her, before attempting to punch Kalib.\\r\\n\\r\\nLuckily a car parked up nearby, spooking the man and he turned and walked off leaving Arry and her son very shaken up.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe incident on July 1 was reported to police and GMP have confirmed they are investigating. Following the abuse, former Haslingden High School pupil Arry said she felt “compelled” to write a blog post about her experience and share it with others.\\r\\n\\r\\nShe said: “Did the man pick on us as we were a easy target – just a young woman and young child? Maybe he thought that I would not stand up for myself possibly. “Did the man not understand that I am British and this is MY country?”\\r\\n\\r\\nShortly after dropping Kalib at school, Arry says she went to Prestwich town centre where she came across an anti-racism gathering that “restored her faith with a tear and a smile”. Arry’s post added: “The rise in racist incidents needs to be addressed. “We need to show a unified front against the few uneducated that think intimidation and fear will achieve a change in their personal situations.\\r\\n\\r\\n“I would love to say that something like this will not happen again unfortunately it will. Things will get worse before they get better.\\r\\n\\r\\n“But remember the vast majority of people are good, they will not stand by and watch this country be dragged down by the ignorance that is on the rise. Lets build communities that work to learn about each other. It is ok that we are not the same.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n“To achieve peace you have to start at grass root levels. Talk in kind, act in kind, educate and nourish the mind to appreciate one another, it is the only way we mould the future for the better. Politics, governments and referendums, will come and go but children are the future, show them the way.”\\r\\n\\r\\nPolice say the man was described as being white and in his early 20s. He had short blonde hair and was wearing a black jacket with grey/black tracksuit bottoms. Anyone with information is asked to contact police on 101.\\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post-Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater Manchester\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-03T16:58:10.872Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-08-07T03:04:37.357Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_p