ormant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":392,\"lat\":\"54.08535\",\"lng\":\"-0.198802\",\"date\":\"2016-07-13T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Bridlington\",\"description\":\"Called a Pole\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"East Riding of Yorkshire\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-29T20:48:39.882Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-07-29T22:09:39.120Z\",\"support\":\"No\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":399,\"lat\":\"50.719164\",\"lng\":\"-1.880769\",\"date\":\"2016-06-28T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Bournemouth\",\"description\":\"A YOUNG child playing in a Bournemouth park has become the latest victim of racist abuse in Dorset.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe Polish youngster was with her family at Queens Park when other children started shouting: \\\"Speak English, speak English\\\" said Adnan Chaudry, Chief Executive of the Dorset Race Equality Council.\\r\\n\\r\\nIt is just one of a number of incidents reported to the council since UK residents voted to leave the European Union.\\r\\n\\r\\nMr Chaudry said a young man alerted police and the Race Quality Council after being targeted as he walked through Boscombe Gardens.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Three men were shouting 'Are you British?' as people walked past them. He said it felt intimidating although he is actually English.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nMr Chaudry added: \\\"There seems to be an environment of intimidation and I am strongly encouraging people to report any such incidents to the police, whether they have been a victim or have seen an incident.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"I believe that right-wing activists will take advantage of this outcome.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nThere have also been reports that a Big Issue seller in Blandford was the victim of a racially-motivated physical and verbal assault.\\r\\n\\r\\nHugo Mieville, Liberal Democrat Parliamentary Spokesperson for North Dorset, told the Daily Echo: \\\"I am sure that voters from both sides, and of all parties and none, would wish to join me in deploring the recent alleged verbal and physical assault.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Whatever our differences following this contentious event, we all believe in democracy and are all members of the same society.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"In these difficult days we need to live together in mutual respect ad civility and be on our guard against those who seek to fracture and divide our fundamentally decent rural community.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nAnd a Poole resident contacted the Daily Echo to tell how a Bulgarian friend was asked 'Do you have your bags packed?' when he went into a shop.\\r\\n\\r\\nDorset County Councillor Pauline Batstone, Champion for Diversity, is also part of KnowStur in Sturminster Newton, where many migrants live and work.\\r\\n\\r\\nShe told the Daily Echo: \\\"We are aware that racism may be a risk at the moment and will be monitoring the situation.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"We are concerned about verbal attacks although the migrants here play a major part in our economy and bring a lot to the cultural life of Sturminster Newton.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nAcross the UK racist attacks appear to have risen with more hatred displayed via social media.\\r\\n\\r\\nA spokesman for anti-racism campaign HOPE not hate, said: \\\"The authorities and police must bring the full force of the law to bear against those who seek to exploit the referendum to promote an agenda of racial or religious hatred.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nAssistant Chief Constable Mark Cooper of Dorset Police said there has been no recorded increase in hate crime but pledged to \\\"respond robustly to any incident.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nHe said: \\\"All forms of hate crime are unacceptable in any circumstances. Hatred not only has the potential to cause serious physical and emotional harm, it damages communities and undermines the diversity and tolerance we should be instead celebrating.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Tackling hate crime is a priority for the Force and we are working with our communities and partners to stamp it out.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nHe said hate crime is known to be under-reported and urged victims to speak out.\\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Bournemouth\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T09:25:48.710Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-07-30T13:32:07.101Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":397,\"lat\":\"51.513434\",\"lng\":\"-0.183801\",\"date\":\"2016-06-29T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"City of Westminster\",\"description\":\"A Brexit supporter screamed ‘we voted to take our country back’ as she destroyed a hijab sculpture at The Royal College of Art days after the EU referendum. Mikaela Haze, 70, shouted ‘Saudi Arabia go home’ and ripped the veil off the £6,300 artwork before knocking it over at the exhibition on 29 June. The sculpture, which consisted of a hijab over a metal frame, was ironically created by masters student Yasmeen Sabri to ‘promote tolerance and understanding’. \\r\\n\\r\\nSource:  http://courtnewsuk.co.uk/brexit-supporter-trashed-hijab-sculpture/\\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T09:23:40.979Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-07-30T13:33:04.407Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":396,\"lat\":\"51.37768\",\"lng\":\"-2.35702\",\"date\":\"2016-06-25T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Bath\",\"description\":\"On the platform at Bath Spa yesterday. “We’re out the EU now, fucking foreigners can all fuck off\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nReferring specifically to Brexit / the referendum\\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"region\":\"Bath and North East Somerset\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T09:21:55.408Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-07-30T13:33:49.841Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":403,\"lat\":\"51.507529\",\"lng\":\"-0.127692\",\"date\":\"2016-06-27T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"My Armenian friend had some young woman sing God Save The Queen into her face yesterday, smirking.\\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T09:41:28.046Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:44.352Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":504,\"lat\":\"53.481061\",\"lng\":\"-2.242514\",\"date\":\"2016-06-28T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Manchester\",\"description\":\"Yesterday my friend, a doctor, British born of Asian origin, told to \\\"\\\"go home\\\"\\\" for 1st time in her life, in Urmston, Greater manchester\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater Manchester\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Helen Pidd\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-01T11:01:53.406Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:44.475Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":502,\"lat\":\"53.480801\",\"lng\":\"-2.242879\",\"date\":\"2016-06-29T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Manchester\",\"description\":\"Another friend racially abused today in Manchester. Born \\u0026always lived \\u0026worked in UK as a doctor. He is devastated. This has to stop.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater Manchester\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Dr Zoe Norris\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-01T10:59:43.482Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:44.498Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":599,\"lat\":null,\"lng\":null,\"date\":\"2016-07-24T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Reading\",\"description\":\"Going home tonight, I was walking from Reading station to the separate ticket section of the station when a half drunk man stared at me and walked towards me and said 'Good we got Brexit now, more space for English people to get rid of people like you' I guess he thought a petite Asian woman was a good target. .. I was very shocked because I have not experienced racist abuse hurled at me since like primary school'... ' Victim received support/ kind words from a French stranger - reported the incident to the police when she got home \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"region\":\"\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-09T12:46:57.976Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-08-09T22:22:40.144Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":493,\"lat\":\"53.745671\",\"lng\":\"-0.336741\",\"date\":\"2016-06-30T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Hull\",\"description\":\"I'm a Romanian living and working in the North of England (Hull), so I normally am on the receiving end of racist comments on a weekly basis, but on the Friday after the Referendum things got really bad...\\r\\nNormally I don't get involved into this kind of discussions, but Friday has been a very weird day for me: on the bus on my morning commute and have ALREADY been the target of 3 separate racist comments. That's 3 individual people who took it upon themselves to not-so-kindly let me know that they have voted Leave to prevent people like me from simultaneously stealing their jobs AND taking all of their benefits. Every single one of them, even the ones I don't need. I'm taking all of them away from hardworking citizens. \\r\\nIs this a sign of things to come, England? Is this how this country is going to look like in the years to come? A country that places more value on where one is from than on their abilities, skills, talents and -ultimately- their basic dignity as a human being?'\\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-01T09:14:27.365Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-08-01T11:06:39.991Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":491,\"lat\":\"51.44999\",\"lng\":\"-0.04548\",\"date\":\"2016-06-28T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Honor Oak Park\",\"description\":\"Spanish and Turkish restaurants in Lewisham had their windows smashed last night in what is being called the latest example of migrants being targeted in the wake of the Brexit vote.\\r\\nFive days on from the historic vote which split the country in two, there has been a rise in reported incidents of racism apparently fuelled by the result.\\r\\nOn Sunday, suspected racist graffiti was found on the front of the Polish Social and Cultural Association in Hammersmith in west London. Neither the POSK nor the Metropolitan Police would confirm the content of the message, which has since been washed way.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis morning, Andrew Burgin posted a picture on Facebook of the damage to Donde Tapas in Honor Oak Park in Lewisham, south-east London.\\r\\nUsers suggested the attack may be the latest example of anti-migrant violence in the wake of the Brexit vote, though this has not been confirmed.\\r\\nOn the community forum for Forest Hill and Honor Oak, local residents confirmed that the Honor Oak Café had also been damaged. Some users claimed the damage had the markings of an attempted theft.\\r\\nYesterday, Prime Minister David Cameron said he would ‘not tolerate intolerance’ following the reported spike of 57% in hate crimes and abuse. He called on Britain to ‘remember these people have come here and made a wonderful contribution to our country.’\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nRead more: http://metro.co.uk/2016/06/28/spanish-and-turkish-restaurants-in-lewisham-have-had-their-windows-smashed-5970826/#ixzz4D4VHAb6Y\\\"\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-01T09:06:54.867Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-08-01T11:07:12.953Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":412,\"lat\":\"52.406822\",\"lng\":\"-1.519693\",\"date\":\"2016-06-29T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Coventry\",\"description\":\"BBC journalist Trish Adudu reported witnessing a white man telling an Asian man to \\\"go home\\\" and then he turned to her and shouted \\\"that goes for you N*****!\\\"\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"West Midlands\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T09:57:16.554Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-07-30T13:27:19.080Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":411,\"lat\":\"50.263195\",\"lng\":\"-5.051041\",\"date\":\"2016-06-30T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Truro\",\"description\":\"I am in Cornwall. Just heard someone say \\\" the bastards are saying we may have to wait 2 years to chuck the black bastards out\\\".\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Cornwall\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T09:53:33.693Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-07-30T13:27:27.980Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":409,\"lat\":\"51.481581\",\"lng\":\"-3.17909\",\"date\":\"2016-07-06T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Cardiff\",\"description\":\"Racist vandals scrawled ‘Muslims are scum’ on a refugee family’s front door in Cardiff, Wales, on Wednesday night, and left knives stabbed in their lawn. The chilling vandalism and implied threat come amid a spike in post Brexit referendum hate crime. A large knife and a medium sized one were found wedged into the ground, along with the racial abuse painted in red on the door. Onions were also apparently thrown at the windows, Wales Online reports.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe Egyptian family of six moved into their new home in the Llanedeyrn neighborhood in April, and have been subjected to constant threats both verbally and physically ever since. The father of the family told Wales Online his oldest son had been dragged off his bike by two children and his wife had been called names like “Muslim raghead” and had the f-word used against her.\\r\\n\\r\\nHe said he is appalled at the magnitude of racist hatred they are subjected to and that the family feel apprehensive about stepping outside, to the extent they feel imprisoned in their own home.\\r\\nWe are very scared. My children are frightened of going outside. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Cardiff\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T09:51:01.301Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-07-30T13:28:24.822Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":407,\"lat\":\"51.551706\",\"lng\":\"-0.158826\",\"date\":\"2016-07-02T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London Borough of Camden\",\"description\":\"Anon tweet 'Spotted in Camden, welcome to post referendum Brexit Britain'- image of a phone box (?) with 'white zone- national action' stickers on it and image of Heil Hitler salute \\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T09:47:52.785Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-07-30T13:29:10.219Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":406,\"lat\":\"51.512344\",\"lng\":\"-0.090985\",\"date\":\"2016-06-27T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"This morning in the City: some stranger told a (white, South African) colleague to 'go home'. a) moron, b) WHAT.\\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T09:45:51.894Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-07-30T13:29:28.890Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":401,\"lat\":\"51.504286\",\"lng\":\"-3.576945\",\"date\":\"2016-07-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Bridgend\",\"description\":\" (1/2)\\r\\nWilliam Rice, 17, from Bridgend , said a man shouted “Brexit” at him while he was on his way to school in his uniform and then told the Brynteg Comprehensive pupil he’d “voted to get your kind out of here”.\\r\\n http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/local-news/white-level-student-beard-been-11552569\\r\\nA white A-level student with a beard has been racially abused since the UK voted to leave the EU. William Rice, 17, thinks he may have been mistaken as Muslim because of his beard. \\r\\nWilliam Rice, 17, from Bridgend , said a man shouted “Brexit” at him while he was on his way to school in his uniform and then told the Brynteg Comprehensive pupil he’d “voted to get your kind out of here”.\\r\\n\\r\\nLater the same day, William said a man drove past him in a white van and shouted: “Go back home you p*** Muslim immigrant.”\\r\\n\\r\\nWilliam, from Waunscil Avenue, Bridgend, is white and believes he has been targeted because of his beard as racial hate crimes have risen across the UK in the wake of the Leave campaign’s victory in the referendum.\\r\\n\\r\\nHe said the incidents, on Monday, June 27, have left him acutely aware of “these horrible people that are racist towards anyone”.\\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Bridgend\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T09:33:48.180Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-07-30T13:31:16.564Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":405,\"lat\":\"51.507143\",\"lng\":\"-0.127456\",\"date\":\"2016-06-29T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"\\\"So, I was called a nigger today. I was on the phone, going through the turnstiles at Elephant. It was busy and someone asked the woman behind me if we'd all fit in the lift. She replied, \\\"\\\"If this fucking nigger gets off her fucking phone, we might.\\\"\\\" Wait, what? For me - and I acknowledge I have been blessed never in my life to have experienced this directly before - these were first time feels. My body instantly wanted to be as far away as possible. My eyes wanted to stare her down. My heart wanted to both break and thunderously roar with rage. My lips couldn't speak but my tongue wanted to say, nah luv, there is no space big enough for both of us to fit, there's no world big enough for me and you and all your pettiness and all your hate. I looked at her. She was pregnant, quite heavily, with empty, unimaginative Daily Mail eyes and a grim, hollow, unreachable stare, and she sat on the tube with her squinty, brittle, pockmarked husband and they downed a magnum of Smirnoff Ice and cussed and grumbled all the way to Bank. And I realised that she was too pathetic and lost to deserve my pain.\\r\\nWe live in a divided world. Whether you are just suddenly reeling at the acknowledgement of this or whether you have always known it, felt it, experienced it, suffered from it, we must not park our collective reactionary response at anger, anguish, resentment, cynicism, or entrench ourselves deeper within our categorised comfort zones. We must all play our part in disembowelling this monstrous invention of whiteness. Racists and bigots, they're the metastases. We have to get to the cancer. We must dismantle the dominant narratives that fuel white supremacy and confront directly the systems of power that insist and thrive on keeping it alive. We must confront ourselves. We must all acknowledge what it has offered to us and what it has kept from us by virtue of the colour of our skin, the colour of our passport, where we exist in the world and on the neoliberal economic ladder. We must empathise, listen to each other's stories, believe them. We must allow each other time to catch up, without malice or scorn. But seriously, do dig deep and catch up. If you don't know, go know. We owe it to ourselves, to each other, to our futures to do this. Let's take this collectively shitty feeling and do the work. We live in this world together. We must fight for it together. As Baldwin said: 'People who shut their eyes to reality simply invite their own destruction, and anyone who insists on remaining in a state of innocence long after that innocence is dead turns himself into a monster.\\\"\\\" This could be the threshold for something new, more alert, less inert. We're all here. Don't be a bystander.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T09:44:26.110Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:44.683Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":404,\"lat\":\"51.507458\",\"lng\":\"-0.127481\",\"date\":\"2016-06-27T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"\\\"My friend's kids, who are black and British, had \\\"\\\"so long, farewell\\\"\\\" sung to them all day at school yesterday. I want my country back.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Owen Barder\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T09:43:05.411Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:44.707Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":602,\"lat\":null,\"lng\":null,\"date\":\"2016-08-06T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Dublin\",\"description\":\"Two girls in a weekend break were told to fuck off out of the EU and get back to England.\\r\\nI thought it outrageous and challenged the rude man, but he told me to fuck off too if I didn't like it\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"region\":\"\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-10T15:28:16.959Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-08-10T15:28:16.959Z\",\"support\":\"I did.\\r\\nSome other people said stuff but I couldn't make out what due to their strong Irish accents\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":393,\"lat\":\"51.502998\",\"lng\":\"-0.280346\",\"date\":\"2016-07-11T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Gunnersbury Lane\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"I think I have just experienced anti-semitism on the Picadilly line. At Acton Town elderly pensioner sits next to me. Asks me 4 times consecutively 'Are you Jewish' Why what difference would it make if I was.? Silence... Most all the carriage heard no one reacted. Silence! Fourth time he asks, my reply why do you want to know? 'Because you have one of those long bended noses. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"W3 8HN\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"i