ard to express my dissatisfaction of his behaviour. Also, to point out he doesn't have to face this alone and such actions are expected to be condemned by most if not all of people in the area.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":639,\"lat\":\"51.48512\",\"lng\":\"0.110733\",\"date\":\"2016-07-05T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Coltness Crescent\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"Neighbour who lives below me went on a racist outburst black neighbours living below him.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"SE2 0UY\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-10-11T11:51:13.108Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-10-12T11:35:04.561Z\",\"support\":\"I called the police. They said they would come out but didn't. Eventually got a call a month later asking whether it had happened again.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":640,\"lat\":\"51.500653\",\"lng\":\"-0.085317\",\"date\":\"2016-10-12T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Weston Street\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"A woman yelled at a man: \\\"Go back to your own country - you immigrant bastard\\\".\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"SE1 4DJ\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-10-13T22:04:36.747Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-10-18T14:46:55.053Z\",\"support\":\"I asked her why she said that to a fellow human in her neighbourhood.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":641,\"lat\":\"56.003876\",\"lng\":\"-4.731757\",\"date\":\"2016-10-02T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"East Princes Street\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Helensburgh\",\"description\":\"An incident of racial abuse on a train is being probed by transport police.\\r\\n\\r\\nOfficers said a man got on the 7.55pm Helensburgh Central to Edinburgh service on Sunday October 2 and started to use his phone. He went on to make comments about a nearby passenger which other people on the train perceived to be racist.\\r\\n\\r\\nSource:  Edinburgh Evening News.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"G84 7QF\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Argyll and Bute\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-10-15T10:06:12.418Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-10-18T14:47:07.529Z\",\"support\":\"other passengers.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":643,\"lat\":\"54.719261\",\"lng\":\"-1.507209\",\"date\":\"2016-10-10T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"1 Kenmir Buildings\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Coxhoe\",\"description\":\"My house mate Anas Bisu heard loud banging on the back door of our house at 8:00 pm and asked who is there. There was loud banging couple of more times on the front door. Anas noticed kids wearing hoodies by turning off the lights in his room upstairs. One of the kids noticed Anas, and everyone took off before Anas could record them. This time there were 4 or 5 kids.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"DH6 4EE\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"County Durham\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Rangarajan Radhakrishnan\",\"created_at\":\"2016-10-19T09:20:57.474Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:46.138Z\",\"support\":\"This time Anas called the police immediately and the police recorded the event.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":645,\"lat\":\"54.719249\",\"lng\":\"-1.50746\",\"date\":\"2016-10-14T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"1 Kenmir Buildings\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Coxhoe\",\"description\":\"I heard soft knocking on my back door, once or twice. I was about to open the door, while my house mate, Anas, shouted, \\\" Who is there?\\\" Then, I tried to look out of the window, and I was surprised by a rain of small pebbles at my window.\\r\\nThere was knocking again on the front door.\\r\\nAnas went to his room upstairs, looked down the window at the kids, while I was making a call to 101.\\r\\nAnas shouted at the kids, \\\"Wait there! If you are stupid enough to stay wait there! I am coming down!\\\"\\r\\nHe came down and conferred with me, but did not go outside the house.\\r\\nI called the landlady at 8:06. The police at 8:11 according to my phone record. All this time, there were 5 or 6 kids around our house trying to annoy us.\\r\\nAnas even noticed the kids vandalising some signs down the road, and the landlady also noticed a few kids with hoodies on the street.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe turned off our lights and waited for the kids to come back, so that we may have chance of identifying or recording them. But they did not come back.\\r\\n\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"DH64EE\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"County Durham\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Rangarajan Radhakrishnan\",\"created_at\":\"2016-10-19T09:27:13.263Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-10-19T14:49:29.882Z\",\"support\":\"The landlady, and our neighbours offered us plenty of support. The police visited us on Monday and reassured us that they will go and talk to the kids based on our previous reports.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":647,\"lat\":null,\"lng\":null,\"date\":\"2016-10-02T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"76 Duke St\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Edinburgh\",\"description\":\"I was shopping in tescos when a strange man with a long coat barged past me, he had his hood up and muttered that I \\\"have to go back once we form the white ethnostate.\\\" He was pushing a trolley filled with those old glass bottles of coca cola and continued talking to himself about what he called \\\"paki scum who should kill themselves.\\\" I was shocked and only thought afterwards of reporting it to the police.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"EH6 8HL\",\"country\":\"\",\"region\":\"\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-10-27T17:16:39.202Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-10-27T17:16:39.202Z\",\"support\":\"No one offered support, some men in skull masks started chanting some numbers over and over again\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":646,\"lat\":\"51.494719\",\"lng\":\"-0.14362\",\"date\":\"2016-09-17T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"I'm a white Australian working in Kent as a teacher. I was catching up with another Australian friend in a pub in London. A middle aged man standing next to us heard or accents told us we weren't welcome in \\\"his country\\\" and to f*** of bank to our own country. We were shocked and told him to go and sit down with his 10 year old son who was also present. At this point he offered to fight us. We politely declined and spoke to the manager who did nothing, didn't even speak to the man. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"SW1V 1JT\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Joe\",\"created_at\":\"2016-10-22T07:13:43.782Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-10-31T16:35:01.912Z\",\"support\":\"There were people all around us. There was a bit of commotion so I'd be surprised if no one noticed, but no one did anything. \",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":161,\"lat\":\"54.97829\",\"lng\":\"-1.617483\",\"date\":\"2016-06-24T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Davy Bank\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Newcastle upon Tyne\",\"description\":\"I was at work chatting about how the media has misled people about refugees and one of my supervisors said the refugees were rats and should be shot at our border until they turn back. Then I got in a heated argument about dehumanizing a minority group and that it was racism.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"NE28\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Tyne and Wear\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-03T12:09:32.980Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:37.342Z\",\"support\":\"Nope except my other supervisor joined in to add that he believed we should get all the refugees on a bout in the channel then sink it. I had to explain to them that they could lose their jobs if I made a formal complaint which shut them up for the time.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":160,\"lat\":\"55.953578\",\"lng\":\"-3.188338\",\"date\":\"2012-08-07T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"North bridge\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Edinburgh\",\"description\":\"While using ATM someone shouted ''Fucking Polish''\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Edinburgh\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-03T12:08:23.021Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:37.410Z\",\"support\":\"Nobody \",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":648,\"lat\":\"50.768035\",\"lng\":\"0.290472\",\"date\":\"2016-10-28T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Howard Square\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Eastbourne\",\"description\":\"I've travelled to Eastbourne from Medway for a little holiday with my boyfriend. Whilst we were having breakfast this morning, being served by two of the three lovely foreign waitresses, a couple in their early thirties sat down at their table. I started listening to the man after an awkward interaction with the waitress. I am a waitress myself so I learn to pay attention to peculiar behaviour. The waitress walked away and the man shortly after said \\\"she didn't have a fucking clue did she? ... She must live here if she has a job, like ...\\\". A while after I tuned in to him ranting to his girlfriend about North London, presumably where he was from, about how he was walking around, speaking to 33 people and only one of them was finally English. \\\"I literally have to speak to 33 people to find someone who speaks fucking English. D'ya know what I mean? And even now, we have to get to the edge of a fucking cliff to find someone English. We have to drive 200 miles to find some guy on the edge of a cliff who speaks English. You can't find anyone who speaks English in this country any more\\\". I felt angry and uncomfortable. I am sure he was speaking loudly deliberately, either to provoke people to react or, worse, because he thought he was speaking for everyone sitting in the room. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"East Sussex\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Becky\",\"created_at\":\"2016-10-28T20:09:16.623Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-10-31T16:35:59.499Z\",\"support\":\"It was only me, my boyfriend and one old man behind me during this interaction. Thankfully the waitress was out of the room. I didn't want to leave in case he said something to her. Her English was good but I wanted to be there to defend her if something happened. If he had said something to her, I would have reacted. Otherwise, it felt like my efforts would be wasted on such a man. Perhaps it is wrong not to stand up and say something at every such opportunity, but I cannot be certain that anyone would have my back. For all I know, the old man behind me shared the same views. That's the sad thing nowadays; I feel like I can't guarantee on bystanders being anti-hate.  I feel like some of them just might agree with his ignorance. \\r\\nI reported the incident to the hotel manager and immediately Googled whether I can report such incidents to the police. I found this website and posted here, feeling that at least I was doing something.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":649,\"lat\":\"54.52361\",\"lng\":\"-1.559458\",\"date\":\"2016-10-29T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"fenthams street\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Richmondshire District\",\"description\":\"4 guys (3 Spanish and 1 Dutch) walking down the main square in town.\\r\\nA group of 3/4 girls start shouting from several meters away something in the lines of \\\"salam malicum\\\" in a rather offensive way towards the Dutch guy (he got curly hair, that likely made the group of girls to think that he was from muslim country).\\r\\nFew minutes later they walked cross us and one of the girls shouts something like: \\\"oh look at him! he is a foreigner but that is OK, we have to take it!\\\" in what appeared to me a patronising and offensive way. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Darlington\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-10-30T09:18:52.938Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-10-31T16:36:18.729Z\",\"support\":\"no one said anything, we just kept walking our way.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":650,\"lat\":\"51.517414\",\"lng\":\"-0.120018\",\"date\":\"2016-11-03T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Kingsway\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"Talking to a friend in Spanish on the eastbound tube platform and a guy comes up to us and tells us to speak English because we're in England.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"WC2B 6AA\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-11-04T07:44:29.605Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-10T16:01:23.161Z\",\"support\":\"No. The guy and his friends walked off straight afterwards, and there weren't other people around so I wouldn't expect someone to, however I did want to report it as I was shocked.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":651,\"lat\":\"52.630886\",\"lng\":\"1.297355\",\"date\":\"2016-11-11T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Sweet briar road\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Norwich\",\"description\":\"Yesterday Nov  10th and elderly man on duke street in front of Norwich arts uni started shouting at me as i crossed the street at the traffic lights, I had headphones in so missed most of what he said. He looked angry was directly staring at me as he shouted. I took my headphones off and heard the last of his comments which were a mix of mumbles and swear words. He then continued walking off.\\r\\n\\r\\nToday Nov 11th I was walking down the road a girl in the passenger seat rolled down her window and shouted either \\\"fucking Paki!\\\" Or \\\"fucking blackie\\\" she then starred at me, laughed and smiled as they drove past. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"Nr6\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Norfolk\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Umi nur\",\"created_at\":\"2016-11-11T18:09:05.233Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-12T18:53:36.314Z\",\"support\":\"Nov 10th- No there was a white girl a few meters behind, she saw and heard eveything she just looked at me in shock. \\r\\n\\r\\nNov 11th- No I was alone. \",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":14,\"lat\":\"52.406871\",\"lng\":\"-1.519629\",\"date\":\"2016-06-29T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Coventry\",\"description\":\"He cycled over to what looked like an Asian student and was basically saying 'Get out of here. Go back home. Haven't you heard the vote?'\\r\\nAnd then he cycles around, sees me looking at him in shock, because it was so loud and so angry.\\r\\nAnd then he says to me 'yeah, that goes for you as well'. He starts calling me the N word and told me to 'go home'.\\r\\n\\r\\nhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-birmingham-36670691\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"West Midlands\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Trish Adudu\",\"created_at\":\"2016-06-30T21:59:55.889Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:34.102Z\",\"support\":null,\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":33,\"lat\":\"51.507407\",\"lng\":\"-0.127691\",\"date\":\"2016-06-24T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"Man called \\\"a Paki cunt in a suit\\\" by a homeless man.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-01T09:44:48.770Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:34.818Z\",\"support\":null,\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":43,\"lat\":\"52.637171\",\"lng\":\"-1.13989\",\"date\":\"2016-06-28T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"2 – 4 Market Place South\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Leicester\",\"description\":\"Young girl asked where she's from. When she answered Poland, asked to pay for a bag (normally free of charge), because \\\"we voted leave and now you have to pay us\\\". \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"LE1 5HB\",\"co