"description\":\"A Ugandan man had a banana thrown at him outside his children's school in a racially motivated attack.\\r\\n\\\"A car stopped alongside me going in the opposite direction.\\r\\n\\\"I looked to my side and saw this man in the driver's seat. The man, who was white, looked at me and seemed to be very angry.\\r\\n\\\"His window was down and he threw a banana at me. My window was closed so the banana just fell to the road.\\r\\n\\\"I began to drive off slowly. I could hear him shouting but could not make out the words.\\r\\n\\\"I was very upset. My 10-year-old son said: \\\"Dad why did that man throw a banana at us?'\\r\\n \\\"I have lived in Leicester for many years and never suffered any racism like this.\\r\\n\\\"There is no doubt it is a racially motivated attack and I think it is because of the Brexit vote.\\r\\n\\r\\nLeicester Mercury. (2016). Banana thrown at Ugandan man in racist incident in Leicester. [online] Available at: http://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/police-investigate-after-banana-is-thrown-at-ugandan-man-in-racist-incident-in-leicester/story-29458553-detail/story.html [Accessed 3 Jul. 2016].\\r\\n\\r\\n\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Leicester\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-03T02:31:03.339Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:37.042Z\",\"support\":\"He reported the incident to the police and to the school. \\r\\n\\r\\nLeicester Mercury. (2016). Banana thrown at Ugandan man in racist incident in Leicester. [online] Available at: http://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/police-investigate-after-banana-is-thrown-at-ugandan-man-in-racist-incident-in-leicester/story-29458553-detail/story.html [Accessed 3 Jul. 2016].\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":170,\"lat\":\"51.507559\",\"lng\":\"-0.127898\",\"date\":\"2016-06-23T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Chalk Farm Road/ Kentish Town Area\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"Landlord calls tenants in the morning after the night of the referendum (Romanian tenants who were sharing a house, one of whom is a pharmacist with a well known high street chemist) to  warn them with obvious hostility in his voice that they have to vacate his property as soon as possible. On being asked why the big haste as the tenancy agreement did not yet expire and they seemed to get along well for many years as well as always paying the rent in time they were told that he doesn't want to rent his property to immigrants anymore.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"N2\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-03T14:41:25.910Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:37.533Z\",\"support\":\"Friends and acquaintances have been informed and asked for help.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":169,\"lat\":\"52.056666\",\"lng\":\"1.148347\",\"date\":\"2016-06-30T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Ipswich\",\"description\":\"Waiting to get on a bus a man said congratulations you are the first English voice I've hear all day. I said I love the diversity don't you? He said I'm trying to wonder where 'they' all come from. I said probably here maybe second or third generation and isn't wonderful to have the gift of being multi lingual. He shut up then.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Suffolk\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-03T13:58:36.423Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:37.573Z\",\"support\":\"I spoke up in a polite a way as possible to make my point. \",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":211,\"lat\":\"54.775528\",\"lng\":\"-1.584579\",\"date\":\"2016-06-25T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"City centre\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Durham\",\"description\":\"My daughters friend, who is bilingual as her mother is German, had to stop speaking in German with her mother in Durham City as people were passing remarks about bloody foreigners.  Durham is a multi cultural University City with funding from University of Japan for its science facilities.  Disgraceful that people should behave in this way.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"County Durham\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-05T10:33:33.440Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:37.987Z\",\"support\":\"People said and did nothing\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":214,\"lat\":\"50.375349\",\"lng\":\"-4.142743\",\"date\":\"2016-06-10T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Plymouth\",\"description\":\"I was stood outside a shop a while back, waiting for my dad to get something and I heard someone foreign walk past two women and they were talking in another language, one of the two women then said 'Why the fuck do we have so many fucking foreigners? Learn to speak English for fucks sake!'\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Plymouth\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-05T13:20:15.320Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:38.099Z\",\"support\":\"No one said anything.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":226,\"lat\":\"53.800667\",\"lng\":\"-1.54906\",\"date\":\"2016-07-05T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Woodhouse\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"City of Leeds\",\"description\":\"A black or mixed race British woman was shouting abuse that included \\\"you'll get deported\\\" and \\\"Fucking go back to where you came from\\\" towards a Muslim woman and her child. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"West Yorkshire\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-05T20:07:02.188Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:38.319Z\",\"support\":\"I reported it and gave a statement to the police who informed the local school about the events to help safeguard the child/children.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":242,\"lat\":\"55.953527\",\"lng\":\"-3.188383\",\"date\":\"2016-07-06T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Middle Meadow Walk\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Edinburgh\",\"description\":\"I was walking past a group of guys who were drinking and talking loudly on Middle Meadow Walk, and a young woman with a head scarf and traditional Muslim dress walked past. One of the guys gestured to her and said something like \\\"look at that one there\\\", and another shouted \\\"take it all off!\\\", in an aggressive way.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Edinburgh\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-06T21:07:13.397Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:38.541Z\",\"support\":\"I said to the guy \\\"Leave her alone\\\". He said \\\"I can have an opinion!\\\". I said again \\\"Leave her alone, please\\\", as the girl walked past them, as far to the other side of the path as possible. I walked away, but looked back to make sure they didn't follow her or anything.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":426,\"lat\":\"51.507364\",\"lng\":\"-0.127698\",\"date\":\"2016-06-26T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"\\\"*Video- description from London Black Revs - link: https://www.facebook.com/LondonBlackRevs/videos/848333021965937/ Racism in the Streets - The Day After the Referendum.\\r\\nFirst racist incident captured since the vote was announced. It only took 2 minutes to bear witness to a Racist with a flag on the outside of his car starts trying to push in front of the queue for petrol. He see's Muslim Cab driver and starts shouting 'Your an Arabic cunt\\\"\\\" over and over. Cabbie starts following him out telling him to go away. The guy gets out of his car and offers to attack him if he gets out of his car. All of this happens in front of a busy petrol station with other Black and Asian drivers filling up. \\r\\n\\r\\nReg Plate - : VX56 UVW. 2006. Silver Vauxhall Insignia.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nsource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T15:33:51.265Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:38.623Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":432,\"lat\":\"51.507144\",\"lng\":\"-0.127957\",\"date\":\"2016-07-17T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"\\\"@kormaqueen  tweeted\\r\\n#PostRefRacism old white lady moves away from my Indian friend on the tube when she sits next to her and sits in between white people.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nSource:PostRefRacism \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T15:40:03.271Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:39.216Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":267,\"lat\":\"51.171792\",\"lng\":\"-0.164652\",\"date\":\"2016-07-05T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Gatwick\",\"description\":\"On Tuesday 5th July I was on the 9am Gatwick to Lanzarote with my two children.  We were in row 2.  Halfway in to the flight, I heard the passenger directly behind me remark to his friend that he'd better start practising the limbo.  When his friend asked why, the man replied, \\\"because it's like being in the Caribbean with those darkies on here\\\".   I'm white, my children are mixed race.  Their father was black, and sadly died of cancer 5 years ago.  Tuesday 5th July would've been his birthday, which was why I chose that date to fly on - to give us a happy memory of the day.\\r\\n\\r\\nThankfully my little girls, who are just 6 and 8 years old did not hear the comments, and so were none the wiser.  I chose not to challenge the man for several reasons - he was big,  built of muscle and as a lone woman with 2 young children, I did not feel comfortable to do so.  And I didn't want my children to experience the potential fallout if I did challenge him. It was extremely upsetting though, and in my 20 odd years of travelling with non-white people (my husband for 15 years and subsequently my children), I have never experienced anything like this.\\r\\n\\r\\nFor the record, when I stood up and looked back in the plane, I could only see white faces.  However, if the plane was 99% black people, that comment would still have been completely unacceptable.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"RH6 0FH\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Surrey\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-09T18:09:54.671Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:39.596Z\",\"support\":\"No, no one did.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":437,\"lat\":\"51.507653\",\"lng\":\"-0.127775\",\"date\":\"2016-07-06T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"Two British homeless camped in an Eastern European woman's corridor. She asked them to leave, but was then verbally and physically abused. They pulled her wrist and knocked her phone out of her hand, all on private property. Police were called several times but never turned up. \\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-30T17:10:33.744Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:39.880Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant