The other banner, also on railings at the park, had the word \\\"hate\\\" and \\\"lies\\\" daubed on it.\\r\\nBoth banners have been taken down by police.\\r\\n\\r\\nA police spokesperson said: \\\"At about 7.30am on June 29 police received a call from a member of the public who reported having seen banners sprayed with graffiti in Victoria Park.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Officers attended two separate areas of the park, and the banners, which were fixed onto railings, were taken down.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"The incident is being treated as religious hate crime and enquiries are being carried out locally to identify those responsible for the damage.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"If anyone was in the park and saw the damage take place, or if anyone thinks they know who is responsible, they should contact 101, quoting incident number 62 of June 29.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nResidents in Clarendon Park have produced a replacement banner and posted it on the meshed fencing at the outdoor all-weather football courts at Victoria Park.\\r\\n\\r\\nRead more: http://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/two-banners-promoting-leicester-muslim-prayer-festival-racially-defaced/story-29456940-detail/story.html#ixzz4DoJfOHSQ\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"LE1 7RY\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Leicester\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Leicester Mercury\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-31T11:06:03.075Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:40.927Z\",\"support\":\"Leicester South MP Jon Ashworth said he was disgusted and appalled by the incidents.\\r\\n\\r\\nHe said: \\\"These are disgusting racially aggravated incidents.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"We as a city live together, celebrate together and condemn racism together.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"I have spoken to the police about community leaders about these incidents.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"I would urge anyone who has any information about these incidents to contact the police as soon as possible.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"I would also urge people to report any racist attacks. This xenophobia and racism must be stamped out.\\\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":536,\"lat\":\"55.864014\",\"lng\":\"-4.251626\",\"date\":\"2016-06-26T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Glasgow\",\"description\":\"Neo-nazi stickers have gone up all around the Clyde and Glasgow Green in the last few days. This breaks my heart. (photos uploaded) https://twitter.com/Eeyinnotyouwin/status/747068589488902144\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Glasgow City\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-01T20:07:14.879Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:41.273Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":543,\"lat\":\"51.450108\",\"lng\":\"-0.04576\",\"date\":\"2016-06-27T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\" (1/2) Spanish and Turkish restaurants in Lewisham had their windows smashed last night in what is being called the latest example of migrants being targeted in the wake of the Brexit vote.\\r\\nFive days on from the historic vote which split the country in two, there has been a rise in reported incidents of racism apparently fuelled by the result.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis morning, Andrew Burgin posted a picture on Facebook of the damage to Donde Tapas in Honor Oak Park in Lewisham, south-east London.\\r\\nUsers suggested the attack may be the latest example of anti-migrant violence in the wake of the Brexit vote, though this has not been confirmed.\\r\\nOn the community forum for Forest Hill and Honor Oak, local residents confirmed that the Honor Oak Café had also been damaged. Some users claimed the damage had the markings of an attempted theft.\\r\\nYesterday, Prime Minister David Cameron said he would ‘not tolerate intolerance’ following the reported spike of 57% in hate crimes and abuse. He called on Britain to ‘remember these people have come here and made a wonderful contribution to our country.’ \\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nRead more: http://metro.co.uk/2016/06/28/spanish-and-turkish-restaurants-in-lewisham-have-had-their-windows-smashed-5970826/#ixzz4D4VHAb6Y\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-01T20:21:16.008Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:41.346Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":475,\"lat\":\"52.950284\",\"lng\":\"-1.12608\",\"date\":\"2016-07-23T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Nottingham\",\"description\":\"Witnessed an elderly woman telling someone speaking broken English that it was 'her' country and they didn't belong. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Nottinghamshire\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-31T20:20:11.828Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:42.067Z\",\"support\":\"(not sure)\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":363,\"lat\":\"53.795915\",\"lng\":\"-1.759491\",\"date\":\"2016-07-06T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Thorncliffe Rd\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Bradford District\",\"description\":\"I was racially abused by anti-semites outside my local synagogue\\r\\nthe I was verbally attacked by a gang of middle eastern youths who called me all sorts of names like 'butcher' or 'vampire' or 'monster'\\r\\nI quickly tried to hurry past them as they spat at me and insulted me viciously when a car suddenly came out of nowhere and some racist goys started throwing bacon, chicken nuggets and prawns at us from their car window while yelling racist slogans like 'fuck off we're full' and 'this is our england'\\r\\nthe youths scattered at the sight of the bacon and since shellfish and pork products arent kosher I ended up having to crawl under a nearby mitsubishi verada sedan as it rained streaks of bacon and rotten prawns all around us\\r\\nat this point the youths seemed to have forgotten about me and decided to attack the car carrying the racists who then sped off with one of them pointing their arse out the window and taking a shit onto the street\\r\\nwhile the youths chased the car i quickly scuttled out from under my hiding place over the non-kosher prawns and ran to the Bradford Reform Synagogue where I had to be calmed down by my Rabbi\\r\\nI am absolutely appalled by this behaviour, I emigrated to the UK from Israel 20 years ago to set up my jewelers in Bradford and I am ashamed that the jewish community still has to suffer these racist attacks from bigots\\r\\nI voted leave in the Bremain referendum and I hang an EU flag from my front window right next to my Israeli flag I'm just as British as the next person and I demand to be treated fairly\\r\\nI only hope when the labour party gets back into power that they can fix all these racists and stop their attacks\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"West Yorkshire\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Mr Zedekiah Schwarz\",\"created_at\":\"2016-07-21T18:34:15.752Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:43.112Z\",\"support\":\"When I went to my Synagogue and told them about what happened my community members were all shocked and appalled at what I had just suffered and needless to say the jewish community in Bradford stands with the message of multiculturalism and diversity as it is the only way to defeat these racists\\r\\n\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":488,\"lat\":\"51.53898\",\"lng\":\"-0.14267\",\"date\":\"2016-07-05T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Camden, London Borough of Camden\",\"description\":\" young woman of Bangladeshi parents talking French on phone to boyfriend is spat on in Camden by Brexit \\\"non-racists\\\"\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-01T08:41:47.872Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:43.666Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":482,\"lat\":\"51.507297\",\"lng\":\"-0.128069\",\"date\":\"2016-06-24T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"Witnessed a elderly Muslim woman run into a waiting room at a GP's office shouting 'I am merely a child of God' being pursued by a elderly and intoxicated white man shouting at her. The man then shouted to the whole room 'you need to get back to where you came from, you all do' and as he was being thrown out shouted 'we voted out, they all need to go!'\\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Worrying Signs\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-01T08:13:55.896Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:43.804Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":555,\"lat\":\"52.205084\",\"lng\":\"0.121935\",\"date\":\"2016-06-30T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Cambridge\",\"description\":\"I am Slovakian. we sublet a room to a young polish guy who told us that he was told to \\\"fuck off to his country\\\" when he was getting money at the cashpoint. I guess this must have happened loads of time already. He just brushed it off and is not bothered about it. I live in Cambridge.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe whole brexit thing does have a considerable effect on me. I walk through Tesco or other shop or just pass people and this is the way I think \\\"does this person hate me? or this one? this one looks foreign\\\" which I find comforting. \\r\\nAt the checkout there is someone looking quite foreign and again I am like \\\"yay, he is not going to hate us\\\" I am worried to speak my language in public and keep thinking who of the people around me could be potentially horrible to me.\\r\\n\\r\\nI find this situation irreparable. I hope it will calm down but the mistrust will stay with me (and other people like me I suppose) and I will always be wary around English people and probably won't hurry to make any friends. I keep thinking \\\"about a third of Britain hates me\\\" Some might not admit it and might even be nice and polite on the surface but they will think it. I am paranoid???\\r\\n\\r\\nThank you for being brave and doing this work. As you can see I am not and that is why I want 