ckled by a group of men on another table for being Polish. \\\"Farage says you've got two years to fuck off back to Poland\\\", apparently.\\r\\nThe guy's been in the UK for 20 years an ha a 7 year old son who for all intents and purposes is as much British as me. He told me him and his family were already considering moving elsewhere. A sad time for the UK.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Cambridgeshire\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-03T12:44:41.753Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:45.260Z\",\"support\":\"I did\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":588,\"lat\":\"54.978183\",\"lng\":\"-1.617712\",\"date\":\"2016-06-27T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Newcastle upon Tyne\",\"description\":\"Protesters in Newcastle called for immigration to ‘stop’ and repatriation to ‘start’ following Friday’s Brexit result. (image holding sign reading 'Stop immigration, start repatriation- NF) \\r\\n\\r\\nHuffpost article - http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/post-brexit-racist-attacks-soar-hate-crimes-reported-to-police-increase-57_uk_57714594e4b08d2c5639adcb\\r\\n\\r\\nCharacteristics: Referring specifically to Brexit / the referendum\\r\\n\\r\\nSource: Post Ref Racism\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-04T11:25:02.162Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:45.321Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":579,\"lat\":\"55.95336\",\"lng\":\"-3.188397\",\"date\":\"2016-06-27T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Edinburgh\",\"description\":\"“Get your passport, you’re fucking going home!” That was shouted at me today in Edinburgh when I was on the number 7 bus (759) at around 1.30 pm going to yet another dentist appointment. We were getting off at Salisbury to get onto the 5 when it happened. She was a white woman in her late 40s in the wheelchair space. As I walked past she shouted that at me. I spoke to the driver, he made Lothian Buses aware and then I tried to get a picture of her for evidence and got the number of the bus. She was then shouting at Mark but I ignored that. I didn’t say anything to her. As we finally got off the bus she started making threatening gestures at me, punching and stuff. From where they’d moved to I think they got off at the stop after us. I was shaking for ages and Im still upset. We’re now going to make a statement. I was going to report it anyways but my dentist, bless him, also encouraged me to report it. His practice manager is Polish and she was subjected to racist abuse on Saturday \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Edinburgh\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-08-04T11:06:36.200Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:45.454Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":622,\"lat\":\"55.953282\",\"lng\":\"-3.188596\",\"date\":\"2016-09-06T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Edinburgh\",\"description\":\"Windows smashed in Leith(Polish Shop)\\r\\nPalestinian shop(Che's) on Forrest Rd window Smashed\\r\\nCan't prove it was racially motivated but looks possible if not very likely\\r\\n\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Edinburgh\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-09-10T15:54:20.595Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:45.730Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":624,\"lat\":\"55.953269\",\"lng\":\"-3.188219\",\"date\":\"2016-06-20T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Edinburgh\",\"description\":\"\\\"Lauren Stonebanks was getting off a bus in Edinburgh last Monday when she heard a white woman shout after her: “Get your passport, you’re f****king going home. Stonebanks, 36, an artist and mental health campaigner who has Indo-Caribbean and Scottish heritage and was born in Scotland, said she was shocked by the abuse.\\\"\\r\\n- Herald Scotland.\\r\\n\\r\\n\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Edinburgh\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-09-13T12:03:31.311Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:45.788Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":642,\"lat\":\"54.719431\",\"lng\":\"-1.507673\",\"date\":\"2016-10-08T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"1 Kenmir Buildings, Coxhoe\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Durham\",\"description\":\"Around 10: 30 pm, I was reading a book in the living room and a laser light was shined directly into my eyes through my partly curtained back window, from my a path behind the house. I initially tried to ignore it as kids' prank. After a few annoying flashes, I thought I could scare them away, and proceeded by asking, \\\"who is there?\\\" in a loud voice, after opening the back door. They ran away from the back door.\\r\\n\\r\\nThey once more shined it through my front curtained windows after a couple of minutes. By this time, I was angry, and tried to stare them down by looking at the laser light directly after opening the curtains. They eventually got tired of shining the light, and they ran up Cornforth Lane flipping fingers at me. I couldn't identify them since they were all wearing hoodies, but there were 3 boys and a girl.\\r\\n\\r\\nI walked out of the door, and shouted to them, \\\"What do you want?\\\"\\r\\n They replied \\\"We want your money!\\\". \\r\\nI told them, \\\"Come and get it!\\\"\\r\\nThey said, \\\"We want you dead!\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nAfter this altercation, I went back home.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"DH64EE\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"County Durham\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Rangarajan Radhakrishnan\",\"created_at\":\"2016-10-19T09:18:54.474Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:46.112Z\",\"support\":\"My Landlady, Jacqueline McDougall, who lives next door offered me support and urged me to inform the police. I called the police, and they asked me to report the incident immediately next time around.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":664,\"lat\":\"51.517579\",\"lng\":\"-0.083036\",\"date\":\"2016-12-03T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Liverpool Street\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"I was coming back home from a party in a taxi. The taxi driver, originally from India, started talking about his personal life. He said that he got into the UK after paying to marry a British women. Then, he got the British citizenship and the right to work indefinitely. With this background he felt entitled to make racist comments to Polish workers blaming them for abusing the benefit system. He said that 'Polish people are lazy and take benefits back home'. Clearly, if ever he was oppressed by the system, now he is oppressing others. Ignorance leads to racism, and education to respect.  \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-12-04T11:44:21.912Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-04T11:44:21.912Z\",\"support\":\"I put my personal Spanish background as an example of European person who has the right to come to the UK to work. I told him that I don't need a visa to come to London. \",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":644,\"lat\":\"54.719441\",\"lng\":\"-1.507195\",\"date\":\"2016-10-18T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"1 Kenmir Buildings, Coxhoe\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Durham\",\"description\":\"On Tuesday evening, I was walking back from work at 6:35 pm from Coxhoe church bus stand. There were couple of kids across the Pedestrian foothpath, near Alberto's pizzeria, who waved at me with a smirk. I waved back at them, thinking that they were friendly. \\r\\n\\r\\nThese kids knocked on one of the three houses between the Chinese takeaway next to Alberto's and the hairdressers, and met up with their friend. All of these kids were between ages of 10-14, nearly 5 ft tall. I think one of them might be connected with a bike stealing incident last year, that happened to my previous house mate, Mahavir Sharma. (More details on this incident may be in the police records.)\\r\\n\\r\\nThey then followed me back hollering some insults behind me till I took a turn near Best One store (where there is a CCTV camera outside, I believe). I stopped there, and waited for them to pass me and wanted to ask them why they were doing this to me. \\r\\n\\r\\nI was walking behind them now and asking them:\\r\\nMe: \\\"Are you talking to me?\\\"\\r\\nThem: Laughter, and some jeering.\\r\\nMe: \\\"Why are doing this?\\\"\\r\\nThem: \\\"We want you to go back where you came from. GO BACK to your country!\\\"\\r\\nMe: \\\"I am British Citizen.\\\" (a white lie) \\r\\nThem: \\\"Yeah you are!\\\" ( more jeering).\\r\\nMe: \\\"I have lived here for 15 years! How old are you?\\\"\\r\\nThem:  \\\"Go back to Birmingham!, GO Back to London! We don't want you here in Coxhoe!\\\"\\r\\nMe: \\\"You don't understand that we bring in new ideas, and new thoughts. Do you?\\\"\\r\\nThem: \\\"You live on benefits, don't you?\\\" \\\"Go back\\\"\\r\\nMe: \\\"No, I work at the University. I study physics. I can show you my ID\\\"\\r\\nThem: \\\"Yeah! You make bombs!\\\"\\r\\nMe: \\\"You don't understand, do you? What are you studying?\\\"\\r\\nThem: \\\"We understand English!\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nBy this time we reached the turn near my house, and the kids started walking away. I told them that I will talk to their parents, and they told me that I wouldn't want to talk to them. Then I told them that I will call the police. They told that they will report on me instead and started to record a video on their mobiles, while calling me a paedophile, when I was dialling 101. They ran away when I started speaking with Durham Police.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"DH64EE\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"County Durham\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Rangarajan Radhakrishnan\",\"created_at\":\"2016-10-19T09:22:24.400Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-11-14T20:03:46.166Z\",\"support\":\"My landlady who lives next door offered me support after the incident.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":655,\"lat\":\"51.181803\",\"lng\":\"0.390168\",\"date\":\"2016-11-16T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Church Road\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Tonbridge\",\"description\":\"I was shopping in Waitrose Paddock Wood. I asked the white cis lady stacking shelves if she knew if they had any black beans out back, as the shelf was empty.  She told me (an ethnic minority lgbtqqiaap) that they don't sell them anymore as brexit and trump had 'changed things' and people like me aren't welcome. I was distraught, I felt extremely triggered and began to shake violently. I wrote a letter to the head office and received only a generic letter back. to make matters worse they used my incorrect personal pronouns. Awful awful awful. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"TN12 6EP\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Kent\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-12-01T00:32:06.884Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-01T00:32:06.884Z\",\"support\":\"no. \",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":656,\"lat\":\"51.439213\",\"lng\":\"0.24866\",\"date\":\"2016-11-24T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Watling Street\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Dartford\",\"description\":\"I tried to enter Dartford cash and carry branch the day after the referendum but was called a harlot and impure by the owner. They told me that, post Brexit, women aren't allowed inside unless covered head to toe in black sheets and certainly not without being accompanied by their husband. Prior to the referendum I was welcomed with open arms - even that one time when I was wearing nothing except my bikini. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"DA2 6EW\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"KENT\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-12-01T11:25:19.084Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-01T11:25:19.084Z\",\"support\":\"Somebody may have spoken up but I wouldn't have understood it as I don't speak Arabic. \",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":658,\"lat\":\"53.959804\",\"lng\":\"-1.087426\",\"date\":\"2016-12-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"York\",\"description\":\"Our local window cleaner wont use Poles, what wrong with using poles to clean your windows.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"York\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-12-01T14:15:29.970Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-01T14:15:29.970Z\",\"support\":\"Dont know who to turn to, is there some window cleaner association?\\r\\n\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":659,\"lat\":\"51.507031\",\"lng\":\"-0.127804\",\"date\":\"2016-12-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"I was called 'white trash' and 'honky'\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-12-01T14:23:12.248Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-01T14:23:12.248Z\",\"support\":\"absolutely none\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":660,\"lat\":\"51.007591\",\"lng\":\"-0.93899\",\"date\":\"2016-12-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"East Hampshire District\",\"description\":\"I have to report myself as I had black pudding, bubble and squeak, brown toast and Indian tea in the cafe this morning.\\r\\n\\r\\nI feel embarrassed and sullied by this experience.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Hampshire\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Ted Cooper\",\"created_at\":\"2016-12-01T14:28:02.409Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-01T14:28:02.409Z\",\"support\":\"Nobody spoke up against my vile behaviour.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":661,\"lat\":\"52.205312\",\"lng\":\"0.122016\",\"date\":\"2016-12-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"10 Tallyho Avenue\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Cambridge\",\"description\":\"I say the damndest thing just happened. As I was walking to the local haberdashery I came across a group of strangely brown fellows who refused to doff their caps when walking by their betters. I must say it ruffled my feathers and I needed a glass of port to steady my nerves, what what.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Cambridgeshire\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Lord Reginald Von Humperdink\",\"created_at\":\"2016-12-01T14:31:55.964Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-01T14:31:55.964Z\",\"support\":\"Mildred the locally employed seamstress popped her head out of the window and berated the uncouth beasts for not knowing their place in civilised society.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":662,\"lat\":\"54.061337\",\"lng\":\"-2.153039\",\"date\":\"2016-12-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Craven District\",\"description\":\"I had been rock climbing and was making my way back to my car in Malham, North Yorkshire, when a group of middle aged people in clothes and shoes made from animals started pointing at me and talking amongst themselves seriously. I heard one of them say \\\"you don't see many of them round here\\\" and another one said \\\"good\\\". As I was taking my kit off and putting it in the boot of my car another one said \\\"I bet that's not even his car!\\\" and they all started laughing. Black bastards.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"North Yorkshire\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"FailyScaley\",\"created_at\":\"2016-12-01T14:45:50.088Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-01T14:45:50.088Z\",\"support\":\"Nobody.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":665,\"lat\":\"51.559692\",\"lng\":\"-0.049959\",\"date\":\"2016-12-06T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Rendlesham Road\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"On my walk home, very close to my house, a bunch of kids aged about 9-10 years old from behind a gate just shouted at me to 'go home' and 'go back home'. When I engaged them in conversation, they said that they meant specifically that the part of pavement outside the gate belonged to them and I wasn't allowed to walk on it.\\r\\nGiving these kids the benefit of the doubt and assuming it was just some game and not about overt racism in their minds, how weird is it that the language of telling people to 'go back home' has become so ingrained that those are the words that come out and not 'keep off' or 'get off the pavement'.\\r\\nIt's not the kids who are scary but the parents who are behind closed doors, all the adults who they have heard that language from.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"E5 8PA\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-12-06T19:49:36.722Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-06T19:49:55.376Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":654,\"lat\":\"51.46495\",\"lng\":\"-0.129701\",\"date\":\"2016-11-26T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"I was on the tube and caught a woman's eye so I smiled at her, but then she turned to me and said, \\\"you're not English are you.\\\" I was really shocked and startled and all I could reply at that moment was \\\"yes actually, I am\\\". Then she proceeded to say \\\"no one on this tube is English\\\". I didn't feel I should have to explain my mixed heritage to her so I walked away. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Zara\",\"created_at\":\"2016-11-30T14:10:40.434Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-06T10:50:44.236Z\",\"support\":\"Nobody did anything. \",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":666,\"lat\":\"51.749281\",\"lng\":\"-1.256627\",\"date\":\"2016-12-09T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Saint Aldate's\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Oxford\",\"description\":\"Drunk man on the bus told me and the bus driver to go home, and was shouting at pretty much everyone on the bus. Then proceeded to get off the bus when the driver reported it to community support officers via his comms device, and then he started shouting at people passing him on the street.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Oxfordshire\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2016-12-09T08:42:26.078Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-09T17:49:12.976Z\",\"support\":\"Nobody offered support but I think everyone was being attacked because we were all looking at him and it clearly made him more agitated. Unfortunately nobody filmed it either.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":667,\"lat\":\"51.454583\",\"lng\":\"-0.978188\",\"date\":\"2016-12-10T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"South Oxfordshire District\",\"description\":\"I got on the 9.20pm train from Paddington to Oxford, today 10th December 2016 and as the train was packed I remain standing for a while talking to my friend in Portuguese. As we got to Slough seats became available and we sat down next to a family with two teenager daughters. We didn't notice anything strange until we carried on talking (not loud or discourteously, perfectly acceptable conversation tone) and noticed they were making gestures for people to shut up. They carried on saying \\\"shut up you're giving everyone a headache with that accent\\\", \\\"shut the fuck up\\\", \\\" do they fucking not understand English?\\\" while carrying on with rude manners, one of them farted, generally making us two feel very unwelcome and  unwanted.\\r\\nAll the time we tried to ignore as didn't think it was worth replying to these kind of people. They left in Reading where I also got up to leave and commented this one is \\\"fucking coming out here\\\". My friend couldn't take it any longer and replied saying we understand English but it was rude of them to speak like that as just because we speak a different language that doesn't give them the right to tell us to shut up. \\r\\nWe are very shaken by this, have worked full time in this country for over 5 years paying full taxes, didn't do anything wrong and don't deserve this treatment from anyone having done nothing wrong but to speak my language in public.\\r\\nI very much regret I didn't report it at the site but couldn't pass it without reporting. Brexit is empowering many people to have this type of behaviour and unfortunately today I experienced it in first person. I don't deserve to feel unwelcome in the country I live and work never having claimed a penny from the government and a country which traditions and beliefs I respect. Don't think it's too much to ask to be respected back. I want to believe actions are being taken to make sure these actions are not going to be encouraged and punished, xenophobia is a result of lack of education which these family clearly showed that.\\r\\nI am very upset to end my day in this way, feel powerless and very unfairly treated, this is not the UK I've known and not the country I want to be living in if treated in this way.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Reading\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Ana Vasconcelos\",\"created_at\":\"2016-12-10T23:09:47.208Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-15T10:36:41.406Z\",\"support\":\"The carriage was full and no one spoke a word (in the good old English way...)\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":668,\"lat\":\"51.505156\",\"lng\":\"-0.09727\",\"date\":\"2016-12-17T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Southwark Street\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"Sitting on 381 bus towards Waterloo and White woman mutters something about \\\".....country\\\". I then looked at her and she has a go saying \\\"what are you looking at me for?\\\". So, I said, \\\"I thought you were talking to me\\\". She responds saying \\\"why would I want to talk to you?\\\" I reply saying \\\"sometimes people like to talk to each other, like strangers\\\". She then says again quietly \\\"go back to your own country\\\" My mum heard her and told her that this is her country. She said she wasn't talking to anyone.I told her that you're muttering and telling people to go back to their own country. At this point, she actually stopped talking.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"F.Q\",\"created_at\":\"2016-12-17T18:52:47.630Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-12-18T22:36:52.396Z\",\"support\":\"No. 4-5 people looked around or over but no one else said anything. Although to be fair we were able to handle it ourselves this time.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":669,\"lat\":\"51.599555\",\"lng\":\"-0.100898\",\"date\":\"2017-01-06T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Perth Road\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"A man started shouting incomprehensibly on the W3 bus after two black women with their prams got onto the bus. He then came to the front and spoke to the driver saying 'there are at least 4 darks back there'. I tried to say something to him, but he got off straight away :(\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2017-01-09T16:43:39.303Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2017-01-16T13:16:54.905Z\",\"support\":\"\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":670,\"lat\":null,\"lng\":null,\"date\":\"2016-12-17T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Trafalgar Square,\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"We were told (not quite in these words: a bit more invective!) to go back to where we come from by a chap driving a Bentley. Felt like an extension of the general feeling of Brexit \\\"please leave foreigners, we do not want you here\\\".\\r\\nI am Australian by birth, my wife Swiss and we (us and our 2 children) are all British citizens and work as University educated professionals - NHS physiotherapist and University Professor.\\r\\n\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"WC2N 5DN\",\"country\":\"\",\"region\":\"\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2017-01-09T19:34:49.626Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2017-01-16T13:17:15.959Z\",\"support\":\"No, but then no one was around to hear it.\\r\\n\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":671,\"lat\":\"53.763201\",\"lng\":\"-2.70309\",\"date\":\"2017-01-07T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"City of Preston\",\"description\":\"I was in a pub beer garden with friends, sitting at a shared table. Two drunk men in their early 20s sat down and began to harass my older friend for having long hair, aggressively jeering at him and calling him \\\"Gandalf\\\". I asked them to go away and leave us alone. When they heard my N.Irish accent they began shouting abuse at me, mainly \\\"Pikey\\\" and \\\"Gypo\\\", I'm sorry to say I got upset (I've lived in England 24 years and it's been a long time since anyone called me that) and reacted by shouting that they were idiots, but they stood up leaning over me and continued to shout abuse at me, mocking my accent, shouting \\\"what the fuck are you doing here?\\\" and telling me to \\\"fuck off back to Ireland\\\". \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Lancashire\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2017-01-12T03:54:44.023Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2017-01-16T13:17:36.025Z\",\"support\":\"Different people at the table began to shout at them, men and women, and one man went and got a bouncer who removed them immediately. \",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":672,\"lat\":\"51.527773\",\"lng\":\"-0.086882\",\"date\":\"2017-01-24T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Corsham Street\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London\",\"description\":\"Nothing- TEST\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"N1 6DR\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2017-01-24T09:55:05.429Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2017-01-24T09:55:05.429Z\",\"support\":\"NO-ONE- TEST\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":673,\"lat\":\"54.775376\",\"lng\":\"-1.584626\",\"date\":\"2017-01-24T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Durham\",\"description\":\"I was walking to the bus station behind a drunk white male who was staggering around the street. He was loudly exclaiming phrases such as \\\"Skinheads of England!\\\", \\\"Don't lose the king's colours!\\\", \\\"Nigger lovers!\\\", \\\"Perish them all!\\\" and other disjointed racist slurs against a vatiation of races. A young Asian guy walked towards him and the drunk man leaned towards him and aggressively told him to \\\"Fuck off!\\\".\\r\\nI'm ashamed to say I didn't speak up, but kept close to the drunk man, as many of the students I teach shop in that area and I wanted to be around in case they were targetted. I'd like to think that if he became violent i would step in, but who can tell until you're in that situation.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"County Durham\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2017-01-24T17:02:15.816Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2017-01-30T22:40:18.007Z\",\"support\":\"Nobody said a word, just exchanges glances, myself included.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":674,\"lat\":\"51.734328\",\"lng\":\"0.468983\",\"date\":\"2017-01-27T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Chelmsford\",\"description\":\"I am a British Citizen, born to immigrant parents from Japan and raised in the UK all my life. Today at my sixth form college, inside the crowded school cafeteria, I was confronted by about 10-15 ethnically White British boys and about 4 whitewashed Indian/Pakistanis asking me a question. That question was \\\"when will you go home\\\"? I told them that I was born and bred in this country and the UK is home. The boys told me to stop talking nonsense as you are not like \\\"us\\\". They then started yelling racist remarks at me, such as \\\"sort out your little squinty eyes because we all have normal eyes and you don't\\\", \\\"sort out your flat nose\\\", \\\"does your dad work as a fisherman?\\\", \\\"you lot are taking our education system for granted, paying lower prices for everything like free school meals whereas we Brits have to pay the full fare thanks to you lot\\\" and \\\"go home or to some other country where they speak the ching chong kawaii language\\\". Some of the boys even started talking to me in a mock East Asian accent, for example pronouncing \\\"English\\\" as \\\"Eeengreeesh\\\" and \\\"I have little slit eyes\\\" as \\\"I do have reettre sreet eyes\\\" (they were impersonating Asians). \\r\\nThe boys all started stretching their eyelids and chanting \\\"ching chong kawaii I no speak Engrish!\\\" in a high pitched voice.\\r\\nI asked them if you are saying such things like that about me, why not the other non-white children in the school? Why single me out? (even though to say racist remarks to anyone of any race in my view is unacceptable)\\r\\nThe boys responded by saying \\\"they're English. They all can speak English. You and your family can't.\\\" I speak with a RP British accent.\\r\\nAfter a good 10 minutes, a few more boys came in the cafeteria and the whole room started to chant \\\"GO HOME GO HOME GO HOME\\\", with one of them drawing a caricature of me based on my race, with two lines for eyes and a Chinese rice picker hat.\\r\\n\\r\\nAlso to let you know that one of these boys is in the Debating club at school and when the club had to argue for or against Brexit in assembly in front of the whole school, that same boy said \\\"that the UK should stop importing all the dregs from mainland Europe, especially the Poles\\\". \\r\\n\\r\\n\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Essex\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"Katsuko Ichihara\",\"created_at\":\"2017-01-27T23:14:30.778Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2017-01-30T22:40:12.601Z\",\"support\":\"Nobody, they were all pretty much laughing at me.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":675,\"lat\":\"51.435475\",\"lng\":\"0.041365\",\"date\":\"2017-01-06T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Station\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"London Borough of Greenwich\",\"description\":\"In SE9, two weeks ago, an Eastern European couple was crossing the road, from Mottingham station, coming back from work on Friday. A white male was walking behind them and when he heard they were speaking another language, he increased his pace and literally walked into the man (of the couple) with great force. He then made an extremely aggressive face and said, \\\"Oy, didn't you see me coming, you f****** idiot?\\\" The Eastern European man kept his cool and said somewhat cynically, \\\"No, I don't have eyes on the back of my head.\\\" At this point, the English man came very close to the Eastern European one and hissed, \\\"What did you say? You want a fight, eh?\\\" The Eastern European man's female partner, who was standing silent and tense all the while, quickly turned to her partner, pulled him, said something and they walked away in silence. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":true,\"postcode\":\"SE9\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Greater London\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2017-01-30T16:19:41.433Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2017-01-30T22:40:51.161Z\",\"support\":\"No one.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":676,\"lat\":\"55.969967\",\"lng\":\"-3.221648\",\"date\":\"2015-01-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Ferry Road\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Edinburgh\",\"description\":\"I could see \\\"f**k\\\" Islam\\\" inscribed on many Lothian Buses bus shelters along Ferry Road. This was over 2 years ago and I am not sure if these inscriptions have been removed or not. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Edinburgh\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2017-02-07T18:40:01.198Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2017-02-07T18:40:01.198Z\",\"support\":\"I am not sure if reported this issue to Lothian Buses. I tried to remove inscriptions with no success.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":677,\"lat\":\"55.953454\",\"lng\":\"-3.191602\",\"date\":\"2008-02-10T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"South Saint Andrew Street\",\"house\":\"13\",\"town\":\"Edinburgh\",\"description\":\"I and my partner attended a Job Centre in Edinburgh upon my arrival to Scotland to obtain NIN. We arranged 2 separate appointments, one for each of us. However when I asked Job Centre staff for an interpreter for my partner, member of staff started laughing at us and told they do not provide intrpreters for foreigners. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe truth was, what I found through my employment, that City of Edinburgh Council provide free of charge interpterers in cases like this one.\",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"EH2 2AZ\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Edinburgh\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2017-02-07T18:49:43.173Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2017-02-07T18:49:43.173Z\",\"support\":\"no one.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":678,\"lat\":\"55.953149\",\"lng\":\"-3.188529\",\"date\":\"2008-07-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"\",\"house\":\"\",\"town\":\"Edinburgh\",\"description\":\"One of my colleagues, every time, when he sees me, he keeps asking me when I'm going back home. He also states very openly that I, as a foreigner, am not entitled to free NHS health care, despite paying my NIN contributions. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Edinburgh\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2017-02-07T18:55:45.392Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2017-02-07T18:55:45.392Z\",\"support\":\"No, other colleagues didn't offer any support.\",\"informant_tel\":null,\"informant_permission\":null,\"informant_role\":null,\"type_incident\":null,\"type_incident_other\":null,\"type_location\":null,\"type_location_other\":null,\"reported_to_police\":null,\"approved_at\":null},{\"id\":679,\"lat\":\"55.946975\",\"lng\":\"-3.186188\",\"date\":\"2012-06-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\"address\":null,\"street\":\"Nicolson Street\",\"house\":\"5/8\",\"town\":\"Edinburgh\",\"description\":\"I could witness Lidl's customer making nasty xenophobic comments towards foreign member of staff. I asked her why she did not react. She stated she got used to it. \",\"summary\":null,\"approved\":false,\"postcode\":\"EH8 9BE\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\",\"region\":\"Edinburgh\",\"informant_email\":null,\"informant_name\":\"\",\"created_at\":\"2017-